name: Unidentified_clone_trooper_(Tranquility)
content:
A clone trooper was stationed on the Venator-class Star Destroyer Tranquility around 21 BBY during the Clone Wars. The Tranquility was assigned to escort Separatist leader Nute Gunray, who had been captured on the planet Rodia, back to Coruscant. However, during the voyage, battle droids attacked their ship, infiltrating the Tranquility using boarding ships. This trooper and his clone captain were sent to secure the reactor room, where they did not notice anything unusual. The two clones ordered the WED-15 Treadwell droid 327-T to keep an eye out before heading for the prison level.
The trooper first appeared in "Cloak of Darkness," the ninth episode of the first season of The Clone Wars television series.
